Almost nobody understands what's going on, not even why the whole war was started.
"The vacuum created by the lack of facts," Mr. Englund noted, "was filled with speculations, assumptions, hopes, fears, prejudices, conspiracy theories, dreams, nightmares and rumors."
Beauty and Grief follows individual stories such as Florence Farmborough, an English nurse in the Russian army, and Richard Stumpf, a young sailor serving in the German fleet.
Their stories are all taken from CVs, letters, and other published material.
