By 2017, the public structural deficit will have to fall by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year and, starting in 2017, the public structural deficit of the federal state will not be allowed to exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while both the federal and the municipalities will have to report a balanced budget.
